<item>
            <title>[CXF-1194] Schema Validation &amp; MTOM fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1194</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Enabling mtom &amp;amp; schema validation for a jaws causes problems once xsd:base64Binary is encountered. It appears that the schema validation is applied to the mtom&apos;d xml which will obviously fail schema validation. To my mind if schema-vallidation &amp;amp; mtom are enabled then schema validation should happen before the mtom step and not after.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12382205">CXF-1194</key>
            <summary>Schema Validation &amp; MTOM fails</summary>
